# Easy Array Traversal

The `foreach` loop is designed specifically for iterating over arrays.

For indexed arrays:
```php
foreach ($array as $value) {
    // do something with $value
}
```

For associative arrays, you can also get the key:
```php
foreach ($array as $key => $value) {
    // use $key and $value
}
```

```php
<?php
$colors = ["red", "green", "blue"];

foreach ($colors as $color) {
    echo "Color: $color\n";
}

$person = ["name" => "Alice", "age" => 25, "city" => "Paris"];

foreach ($person as $key => $value) {
    echo "$key: $value\n";
}
?>
```

## By Reference

If you want to modify array elements inside the loop, use reference `&`:

```php
foreach ($numbers as &$number) {
    $number *= 2;
}
unset($number); // break the reference
```
